\pard\f0\fs28 Trees or shrubs. Leaves 2-pinnate and dorsiventral in the juvenile state and remaining so in the adult state or soon reduced to simple phyllodes; stipules rudimentary or becoming large spines. Flowers small, yellow to white, in cylindrical spikes or in globose capitula arranged in racemes or panicles; calyx and corolla 4- to 5-merous; stamens numerous, free, long and conspicuous. Legume usually dehiscent. Seeds with a filiform funicle ending in a cupuliform strophiole.
